				<textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[1]<font color="#000000">: TV stimulates children's interests.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[2]<font color="#000000">: Children have fewer hobbies.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[3]<font color="#000000">: Adults often disapprove of children watching TV.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[4]<font color="#000000">: Parents should check on children's viewing.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[5]<font color="#000000">: Children learn more about the world.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[6]<font color="#000000">: Children are lonelier.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[7]<font color="#000000">: Children should do other activities as well.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[8]<font color="#000000">: TV helps educate children in a variety of ways.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[9]<font color="#000000">: TV â€“ most popular form of entertainment for children.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[10]<font color="#000000">: Children are less sociable.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[11]<font color="#000000">: Children read less.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[12]<font color="#000000">: TV is easier and safer than other forms of relaxation.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><textformat leading="2"><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff" letterspacing="0" kerning="0">[13]<font color="#000000">: TV makes children less imaginative/inventive.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p></textformat><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p><img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/LE_AW_012.jpg" height="250" width="165" mode="1" id="1001"  /><media class="leftFloat" src="../Media/" height="" width="" mode="1" id="2001"  />
